uri Kurds|Muzuri]] tribe by population, in the 2017 Census conducted by '''Muhammadali Sa\u2018id''' Pendroi,<ref>{{cite web|title=Muhamadali Sayid ,2017 Census|url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=1283699921667021&set=a.186742458029445.34902.100000810761354&type=3&theater|website=www.facebook.com|language=en}}</ref> the Village of Pendro recorded a population of 2547, the census revealed the following numbers: 1290 females (50.65%), 1257 males (49.35%). More than half of them living in Bahirka since 1978.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:1em; float:left;\"\n|+Pendroi in [[Iraqi Kurdistan|Kurdistan]] (2017)\n|-\n! Rank\n! Place\n! Households\n|-\n!1\n| Bahirka\n|342\n|-\n!2\n|[[Erbil]]\n|67\n|-\n!3\n|Pirmam\n|59\n|-\n!4\n|[[Soran, Iraq|Soran]]\n|46\n|-\n!5\n|[[Barzan, Iraq|Barzan]]\n|18\n|-\n!6\n|[[Dohuk]]\n|16\n|-\n!7\n|Rezan\n|11\n|-\n!8\n|Ble\n|9\n|-\n!9\n|Syrye\n|5\n|-\n!10\n|[[Zakho]]\n|1\n|-\n!11\n|Selke\n|1\n|-\n!12\n|Gureto\n|1\n|-\n!13\n|Shaneder\n|1\n|-\n!14\n|Shakholan\n|1\n|-\n!'''Total'''\n|'''14'''\n|'''578'''\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:right; font-size:96%;\"  \n|+Pendroi [[Diaspora]] (2017)\n\n! Rank\n! Country\n! Households\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |1\n| [[United States]]\n|10\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |2\n| [[Germany]]\n|8\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |3\n| [[Sweden]]\n| 7\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |4\n| [[Russia]]\n| 5\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |5\n| [[Denmark]]\n| 5\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |6\n| [[Netherlands]]\n| 4\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |7\n| [[UK]]\n| 3\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |8\n| [[Canada]]\n| 2\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |9\n| [[Australia]]\n| 1\n|-\n|'''Total'''\n|'''9'''\n|'''45'''\n|}\n\n===Education===\n\n[[File:Jalal Majid Amin 1968.jpg|thumb|Pendro [[Elementary School]] students and teachers (1968)]]\nAccording to a 2017 census by '''Muhammadali Sa\u2018id''' Pendroi,<ref>{{cite web|title=Pendro village|url=https://www.facebook.com/PENDROVillage/photos/pb.137995939723983.-2207520000.1494309405./598298140360425/?type=3&theater|website=www.facebook.com|language=en}}</ref> Pendro is one of the most educated villages in the [[Mergasor District]]. With over 50 percent of Pendroi adults having attained at least an undergraduate college or university degree.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:1em; float:left;\"\n|+Pendroi students in all Educational stage\n|-\n! Rank\n! Stage\n! Male\n! Female\n! Total\n|-\n!1\n| First Grade to Twelfth Grade\n| 343\n| 310\n| 653\n|-\n!2\n| University\n| 49\n| 52\n| 101\n|-\n!3\n| Educational Institutions\n| 16\n| 17\n| 33\n|-\n!4\n| Doctoral\n| 4\n| 1\n| 5\n|-\n!5\n| Master\n| 1\n| 1\n| 2\n|-\n! '''Total'''\n| '''5'''\n| '''423'''\n| '''371'''\n| '''794'''\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:right; font-size:96%;\"  \n|+ Educational Attainment of the Pendroi\n! Rank\n! Degree & Diploma\n! Male\n! Female\n! Total\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |1\n| University\n| 131\n| 98\n| 229\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |2\n| Institution\n| 65\n| 77\n| 142\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |3\n| Master\n| 14\n| 4\n| 18\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |4\n| Doctoral\n| 4\n| 2\n| 6\n|-\n!style=\"text-align: right;\" |5\n| High Diploma\n| 2\n| 0\n| 2\n|-\n|'''Total'''\n|'''5'''\n| '''216'''\n| '''181'''\n| '''397'''\n|}\n\n==Wildlife==\nEnvironmental protection in Pendro and other parts of [[Barzani Kurds|Barzani]] tribes  began during the leadership of [[Ahmed Barzani|Khudan]], he has banned the cutting of trees and hunting wild animals, especially [[wild goat]] and more progressive environmental protection had it start in the 1990s.\n\n===Flora===\n[[File:17092007Pendro.Sleman,Leyl,Surme,Bengin&Saleh.jpg|thumb|After [[harvest]] the villagers removing [[almond]] hulls, Pendro (2007)]]\nPendro has a hundreds species of plants,<ref name=\"kurdflora\">{{cite web|title=Home {{!}} Kurd Flora|url=http://www.kurdflora.com|website=www.kurdflora.com|access-date=2018-12-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928044312/http://www.kurdflora.com/|archive-date=2018-09-28|url-status=live}}</ref> some of species are introduced and non-native. More than 70% the area of the Pendro is forested, with stands of [[Platanus orientalis|Plane tree]], [[Oak]], [[Quercus infectoria]], [[Chestnut]], [[Pistacia atlantica]], [[Almond]], [[Walnut]], [[Common fig|Fig]], [[Vitis]], [[Pear]], [[Morus nigra]], [[Apricot]], [[Plum]], [[Apple]], [[Pomegranate]], [[Peach]], [[Quince]], [[Sumac]] and other valuable trees. Mountain herbs such as [[Agaricus|Mushroom]], [[Ferulago]], [[Fennel]], [[Allium ampeloprasum|Wild leek]], [[Carduus nutans]], [[Arum]], [[Allium haemanthoides|Allium]], [[Rheum ribes]] and many other mountain herbs. In flowers include [[Narcissus \u00d7 medioluteus|Narcissus]], [[Fritillaria imperialis]], [[Papaver rhoeas]] and other beautiful flowers.<ref name=\"mushroom\">{{cite web|title=Survey and Identification of Mushrooms in Erbil Governorate (PDF Download Available)|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/261551919|website=ResearchGate|language=en|access-date=2017-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928044017/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/261551919_Survey_and_Identification_of_Mushrooms_in_Erbil_Governorate|archive-date=2018-09-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Fauna===\n\n==== Mammals ====\nAnimals that inhabit around the Pendro include [[Brown bear]], [[Syrian brown bear]], [[Persian squirrel|Squirrel]], [[Wild goat]], [[Boar]], [[Gray wolf|Wolf]], [[Striped hyena|Hyena]], [[Golden jackal]], [[Mouflon]], [[European badger|Badger]], [[Crested porcupine]], [[Marbled polecat]], [[Red Fox|Fox]], [[European hare|Hare]], [[Long-eared hedgehog|Hedgehog]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Farhadinia|first1=Mohammad Sadegh|last2=Valizadegan|first2=Negin|title=A preliminary baseline status of the Syrian Brown Bear Ursus arctos syriacus (Mammalia: Carnivora: Ursidae) in Golestanak, Northern Iran|url=http://www.threatenedtaxa.in/index.php/JoTT/article/view/1787/3104|website=Journal of Threatened Taxa|pages=6796\u20136799|language=en|date=26 January 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150814161724/http://www.threatenedtaxa.in/index.php/JoTT/article/view/1787/3104|archivedate=14 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NMNH Department of Systematic Biology, Division of Mammals - Mammal Species of the World Home Page|url=http://nmnhgoph.si.edu/msw/|date=27 April 2007|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070427043030/http://nmnhgoph.si.edu/msw/|archivedate=27 April 2007}}</ref> '''Felidae''' in this family include [[Wild cat]], [[Caracal]].\n\n==== Birds ====\nTens of thousands birds from many species pass through Pendro and surrounding villages during the bi-annual migration season, from [[Caucasus]] and West Asia to south Iraq and south-east Iran in the winter, and back in the spring. Entire region is the stopover point for thousands birds migrating from Caucasus to [[Persian gulf|Gulf]] and migrating [[Common crane|Crane]]s some time take a pause because of bad weather as they travel between breeding and wintering grounds. These are some names of bird species in Pendro and surrounding areas.<ref>{{cite web|title=Iraq bird checklist|url=http://avibase.bsc-eoc.org/checklist.jsp?lang=EN&region=iq&list=clements|website=avibase.bsc-eoc.org|access-date=2017-05-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120922085253/http://avibase.bsc-eoc.org/checklist.jsp?lang=EN&region=iq&list=clements|archive-date=2012-09-22|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Chukar partridge|Chukar]], [[See-see partridge|Partridge]], [[Black francolin|Francolin]], [[Common quail|Quail]], [[Common crane|Crane]], [[Black kite]], [[Griffon vulture|Vulture]], [[Short-toed snake eagle|Eagle]], [[Western marsh harrier|Harrier]], [[Common buzzard]], [[Long-legged buzzard|Buzzard]], [[Greater spotted eagle|Eagle]], [[Golden eagle]], [[Common kestrel|Kestrel]], [[Peregrine falcon|Falcon]], [[Great egret|Egret]], [[Squacco heron|Heron]], [[White stork|Stork]], [[Eurasian teal|Teal]], [[Mallard]], [[Eurasian stone-curlew|Curlew]], [[Common tern|Tern]], [[Rock pigeon]], [[Stock dove|Dove]], [[Common wood pigeon|Pigeon]], [[Common cuckoo|Cuckoo]], [[Barn owl|Owl]], [[Eurasian eagle-owl|Eagle-owl]], [[Brown fish owl]], [[Little owl]], [[European nightjar|Nightjar]], [[Alpine swift]], [[Common swift|Swift]], [[Kingfisher]], [[European bee-eater]], [[Blue-cheeked bee-eater|Bee-Eater]], [[Hoopoe]], [[Syrian woodpecker]], [[European green woodpecker|Woodpecker]], ( eight species of [[Lark]]), [[Eurasian wren|Wren]], [[Alpine accentor|Accentor]], [[Common blackbird|Blackbird]], [[Mistle thrush|Thrush]], [[Song thrush]], ( over four species of [[Warbler]]), [[European robin]], [[Rufous-tailed scrub robin|Robin]], [[White-throated robin]], [[Eurasian blue tit|Blue tit]], [[Great tit]], [[Sombre tit|Tit]], [[Common redstart|Redstart]], [[Rock nuthatch]], [[Persian nuthatch]], [[Woodchat shrike|Shrike]], [[Masked shrike]], [[Eurasian jay]], [[Eurasian magpie|Magpie]], [[Common raven|Raven]], [[Hooded crow|Crow]], [[Common starling|Starling]], [[Yellowhammer]], [[Pine bunting|Pine]], ( at least over six species of [[Bunting (bird)|Bunting]] bird), [[Common chaffinch|Chaffinch]], [[Brambling]], [[European goldfinch|Goldfinch]], [[Twite]], [[European serin|Serin]], [[House sparrow|Sparrow]], there are over 30 species of [[Old World sparrow|Sparrow]] worldwide and eight species which occur in areas.\n\n==== Reptiles and Others ====\nThe following are some of the reptiles of  Pendro, primarily covering the region in northeast [[Iraqi kurdistan|Kurdistan]]. [[Macrovipera lebetina obtusa|Macrovipera]], [[Dolichophis jugularis|Dolichophis]]. [[Montivipera raddei|Kurdistan viper]], [[Testudo (genus)|Testudo]], [[Spur-thighed tortoise|Spur]], [[Ophisops]], [[Carinatogecko|Gecko]], [[Mediterranean house gecko|House gecko]], some other species of [[Snake]], [[lizard]] and [[Turtle]] occur in region. '''Amphibians''' in this [[Class (biology)|class]], [[Pelobates syriacus|Frog]], [[Marsh frog]] and other amphibians. Pendro has thousands of '''Invertebrates''' and '''Invasive species'''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Venomous Snakes In Iraq|url=http://www.reptilesmagazine.com/Snakes/Wild-Snakes/Venomous-Snakes-In-Iraq/|website=www.reptilesmagazine.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170522015018/http://www.reptilesmagazine.com/Snakes/Wild-Snakes/Venomous-Snakes-In-Iraq/|archive-date=2017-05-22|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Iraq Check List|url=https://www.inaturalist.org/check_lists/8811-Iraq-Check-List?page=2|website=iNaturalist.org|access-date=2018-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181030205849/https://www.inaturalist.org/check_lists/8811-Iraq-Check-List?page=2|archive-date=2018-10-30|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Pendro}}\n* [https://pendrovillage.webs.com/ Pendro Website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140717073135/http://hawlergov.org/ku/region.php?id=1330759021 Erbil Governorate]\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Erbil Governorate]]\n[[Category:Geography of Iraqi Kurdistan]]\n[[Category:Kurdish settlements]]\n[[Category:Villages in Arbil Province]]\n", "name_user": "Ashurpedia", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pendro"}
